00:52:25,968 --> 00:52:28,623
-Go down like that?
-ANNA: Yeah.

763
00:52:28,667 --> 00:52:31,887
Yeah, that's nice.
A nice imprint in the forehead.

764
00:52:31,931 --> 00:52:33,062
It's very nice.

765
00:52:33,106 --> 00:52:35,195
Look, Daddy. Look what I did.

766
00:52:35,239 --> 00:52:37,110
The girl and the prince,
they're getting married.

767
00:52:37,154 --> 00:52:38,938
Hmm, very nice.

768
00:52:38,981 --> 00:52:40,722
She's gifted, isn't she?

769
00:52:40,766 --> 00:52:43,856
You know, they say
that talent like this
runs in the family.

770
00:52:43,899 --> 00:52:46,772
-Mommy can't draw.
-[NICK LAUGHS]

771
00:52:46,815 --> 00:52:49,601
[GASPS] Look
what time it is, Christina.

772
00:52:49,644 --> 00:52:52,430
Got to hurry. Come on,
help me clean this up.

773
00:52:52,473 --> 00:52:53,822
What's the rush?
Where are you going?

774
00:52:54,519 --> 00:52:55,781
Anna won't tell me.

775
00:52:55,824 --> 00:52:57,957
It's a surprise.

776
00:52:58,000 --> 00:52:59,741
It's a surprise. Can I come?

777
00:52:59,785 --> 00:53:02,135
Well, it's something special.
Just for the girls.

778
00:53:02,179 --> 00:53:03,789
-Please?
-No.

779
00:53:03,832 --> 00:53:05,269
No boys allowed. Right, Anna?

780
00:53:05,312 --> 00:53:06,879
-That's right.
-I'll wear a dress.

781
00:53:06,922 --> 00:53:07,967
[CHRISTINA LAUGHS]

782
00:53:13,581 --> 00:53:14,843
Goodbye, Nick.

783
00:53:54,492 --> 00:53:56,407
I'm sorry. Are you all right?

784
00:53:56,450 --> 00:53:59,105
Yeah, I'm all right.

785
00:53:59,148 --> 00:54:00,976
Oh, I wish I could say
the same for these.

786
00:54:01,890 --> 00:54:03,152
Who are you?

787
00:54:03,196 --> 00:54:06,286
Bob McDowell.
Bob's Greenskeeping Unlimited.

788
00:54:06,330 --> 00:54:09,420
New gardener. You wouldn't be
Mrs. Cowan by any chance?

789
00:54:10,029 --> 00:54:12,031
Yes.

790
00:54:12,074 --> 00:54:14,512
-Pleased to meet you.
-Hey, what's going on?

791
00:54:14,555 --> 00:54:16,557
I was gonna ask you
the same question.

792
00:54:16,601 --> 00:54:19,604
Mrs. Cowan and I
had a bit of run-in.
I'm afraid I broke your eggs.

793
00:54:19,647 --> 00:54:21,780
That's okay.
We'll deduct it from your bill.

794
00:54:21,823 --> 00:54:23,651
-Okay.
-Let me take one of these.

795
00:54:25,000 --> 00:54:26,698
I'm sorry about that.

796
00:54:26,741 --> 00:54:28,395
-I guess I'll...
-It's okay.

797
00:54:28,439 --> 00:54:30,571
I'll get started on
the chaparral
on the side of the house.

798
00:54:30,615 --> 00:54:31,616
Right.

799
00:54:32,660 --> 00:54:33,879
Who's he?

800
00:54:33,922 --> 00:54:36,534
Only the best landscape artist
in Topanga.

801
00:54:36,577 --> 00:54:39,363
Can we afford this?
I mean, all the rose bushes?

802
00:54:39,406 --> 00:54:41,713
You won't believe
how cheap he is.
I really got to hand it to Anna.

803
00:54:42,801 --> 00:54:44,977
-Anna?
-Yeah.

804
00:54:45,020 --> 00:54:46,500
What does she
got to do with this?

805
00:54:46,544 --> 00:54:48,459
She found him.
She bumped into him
at the mini-mart.

806
00:54:48,502 --> 00:54:51,288
And the next thing you know,
he's reworking his calendar
to fit us in.

807
00:54:51,331 --> 00:54:53,551
-[SCOFFS]
-What?

808
00:54:53,594 --> 00:54:55,117
I mean, this is a big decision.

809
00:54:55,161 --> 00:54:56,467
Don't you think
we should have discussed it?

810
00:54:56,510 --> 00:54:58,120
Honey, you have been bugging me

811
00:54:58,164 --> 00:54:59,992
to clean this place up
since we moved here.

812
00:55:00,035 --> 00:55:02,690
Now, I've been busy,
you've been busy.
I thought you would be thrilled.

813
00:55:03,996 --> 00:55:04,997
I'm thrilled.

814
00:55:05,737 --> 00:55:07,042
Where's Christina?

815
00:55:07,086 --> 00:55:08,261
She and Anna went off
somewhere this morning.

816
00:55:08,305 --> 00:55:09,523
Some big secret.

817
00:55:11,438 --> 00:55:12,526
CHRISTINA: Ooh! Ooh!

818
00:55:12,570 --> 00:55:14,267
NICK: What is this?

819
00:55:14,311 --> 00:55:16,138
CHRISTINA:
We had the best time today.

820
00:55:16,182 --> 00:55:18,053
Anna took me
to Mystery Mountain.

821
00:55:18,097 --> 00:55:20,839
And she bought me this costume,
and I wore it
in the haunted house.

822
00:55:20,882 --> 00:55:22,667
I scared everybody.

823
00:55:22,710 --> 00:55:25,191
I thought we were gonna go
to Mystery Mountain together.

824
00:55:25,234 --> 00:55:28,368
Anna took me today instead.
We went on all the rides.

825
00:55:28,412 --> 00:55:29,369
Hello.

826
00:55:31,110 --> 00:55:33,504
Anna, tell them
about the roller coaster.

827
00:55:33,547 --> 00:55:36,463
ANNA: All right, Chrissy,
we'll tell them all
about your day a little later.

828
00:55:36,507 --> 00:55:39,336
But right now, I want you
to take off the costume

829
00:55:39,379 --> 00:55:41,338
and go and get washed up.

830
00:55:41,381 --> 00:55:42,904
I'll make some dinner.

831
00:55:42,948 --> 00:55:45,298
I'll be making dinner tonight,
Anna, thank you very much.

832
00:55:45,342 --> 00:55:47,082
Please take Chrissy to her room.

833
00:55:48,040 --> 00:55:49,171
All right.

834
00:55:49,563 --> 00:55:50,651
Come on.

835
00:56:04,839 --> 00:56:06,450
What was that all about?

836
00:56:06,493 --> 00:56:08,843
She knew I was planning
to take Christina
for her birthday.

837
00:56:09,496 --> 00:56:11,019
Anna?

838
00:56:11,063 --> 00:56:14,153
Christina has been
talking about it for four weeks.

839
00:56:14,196 --> 00:56:16,198
So what are you saying?
That you think
she did it deliberately?

840
00:56:16,242 --> 00:56:18,940
I don't know what to think.
Where are my saucepans? Anna!

841
00:56:18,984 --> 00:56:20,942
-Would you calm down?
-I am calm, Nick.

842
00:56:21,378 --> 00:56:22,379
Anna!

843
00:56:23,467 --> 00:56:24,555
Anna!

844
00:56:24,598 --> 00:56:25,860
Yes, Mrs. Cowan.

845
00:56:26,687 --> 00:56:28,254
Where are my saucepans?

846
00:56:28,297 --> 00:56:29,690
The saucepans are...

847
00:56:29,734 --> 00:56:32,040
Well, I put them in the cabinet
over the stove.

848
00:56:32,084 --> 00:56:34,086
Did I ask you
to rearrange my kitchen?

849
00:56:34,129 --> 00:56:36,697
No, but I just thought that
it might be more efficient.

850
00:56:36,741 --> 00:56:38,743
My kitchen
was perfectly efficient before.

851
00:56:38,786 --> 00:56:42,529
I want things where I put them,
not where you think they belong.
All right?

852
00:56:42,573 --> 00:56:44,313
Yes, of course.

853
00:56:44,357 --> 00:56:46,054
And were you also aware
that I had plans

854
00:56:46,098 --> 00:56:48,056
to take Christina
to Mystery Mountain
for her birthday?

855
00:56:48,753 --> 00:56:50,232
No, I was not.

856
00:56:50,276 --> 00:56:51,451
Chrissy didn't tell you?

857
00:56:51,495 --> 00:56:53,105
No. I had no idea.

858
00:56:54,367 --> 00:56:56,456
I'm sorry
if I ruined your plans.

859
00:56:56,500 --> 00:56:58,197
It was not my intention.

860
00:56:58,240 --> 00:56:59,503
Fine.

861
00:56:59,546 --> 00:57:01,374
In the future,
I expect you would check with me

862
00:57:01,418 --> 00:57:03,071
before you go on another one
of your secret outings.

863
00:57:03,115 --> 00:57:04,290
Is that understood?

864
00:57:04,595 --> 00:57:05,552
Yes.

865
00:57:08,903 --> 00:57:09,904
I'm sorry.

866
00:57:15,780 --> 00:57:17,869
Damn it!

867
00:57:17,912 --> 00:57:19,784
Don't you think
you are overreacting
just a little bit?

868
00:57:19,827 --> 00:57:21,133
Oh, I'm overreacting?

869
00:57:22,047 --> 00:57:23,352
Fine.

870
00:57:23,396 --> 00:57:24,571
Then you make dinner.

871
00:57:25,877 --> 00:57:27,269
I'm gonna take a nap.

872
00:57:56,516 --> 00:57:57,604
CHRISTINA: Mommy?

873
00:57:58,344 --> 00:57:59,345
Mommy.

874
00:58:01,956 --> 00:58:03,305
Mommy, come on.

875
00:58:04,611 --> 00:58:05,656
Mom, wake up.

876
00:58:07,266 --> 00:58:08,267
Mommy.

877
00:58:10,748 --> 00:58:11,749
Mom.

878
00:58:13,315 --> 00:58:14,491
Mommy.

879
00:58:14,534 --> 00:58:15,535
What?

880
00:58:15,579 --> 00:58:17,319
CHRISTINA: Dinner's ready,
come on.

881
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:20,801
Okay.

882
00:58:23,456 --> 00:58:24,457
I'm coming.

883
00:58:33,727 --> 00:58:35,599
CHRISTINA: Ooh, ooh!

884
00:58:35,642 --> 00:58:37,383
Ooh, ooh!

885
00:58:37,818 --> 00:58:38,950
Ooh!

886
00:58:38,993 --> 00:58:40,734
KATE: Why are you
still wearing that?

887
00:58:40,778 --> 00:58:42,127
Come on, Mom.
It's a surprise.

888
00:58:42,170 --> 00:58:43,520
What's with the lights?

889
00:58:44,825 --> 00:58:46,914
I don't like surprises.
Nick?

890
00:58:48,002 --> 00:58:49,003
Nick?

891
00:58:49,700 --> 00:58:51,353
Turn on the lights.

892
00:58:51,397 --> 00:58:55,575
NICK: Come on, honey,
we're just playing. It's a game.

893
00:58:55,619 --> 00:58:57,577
CHRISTINA: 
♪ Here we go round 
The mulberry bush

894
00:58:57,621 --> 00:58:59,536
♪ The mulberry bush 
The mulberry bush

895
00:58:59,579 --> 00:59:01,146
♪ Here we go round 
The mulberry bush

896
00:59:01,189 --> 00:59:02,626
♪ So early in the morning

897
00:59:02,669 --> 00:59:03,801
♪ Here we go round 
The mulberry bush ♪

898
00:59:03,844 --> 00:59:06,412
Chrissy, stop.
Enough is enough.

899
00:59:06,455 --> 00:59:08,501
Nick, turn on the lights.

900
00:59:08,545 --> 00:59:09,589
Come here, sweetheart.

901
00:59:10,329 --> 00:59:11,373
Come here.

902
00:59:15,421 --> 00:59:19,381
♪ Kate's not wanted anymore

903
00:59:19,425 --> 00:59:23,429
♪ Gonna throw her 
Out the door ♪

904
00:59:23,472 --> 00:59:24,822
[NICK LAUGHING]

905
00:59:30,001 --> 00:59:31,568
Are you crazy?

906
00:59:31,611 --> 00:59:34,309
What are you doing?

907
00:59:34,353 --> 00:59:38,052
Perhaps some lingonberry wine
before dinner, Mrs. Cowan?

908
00:59:43,667 --> 00:59:45,756
Stop it. Please.

909
00:59:45,799 --> 00:59:47,888
ANNA: What's the matter, Katie?

910
00:59:47,932 --> 00:59:49,934
Don't you like the way
it tastes?

911
00:59:49,977 --> 00:59:52,632
-[NICK LAUGHING]
-I made it especially for you.

912
00:59:56,027 --> 00:59:57,202
[GASPS]

913
00:59:58,203 --> 00:59:59,813
[INDISTINCT LAUGHTER]

914
01:00:14,611 --> 01:00:16,090
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

915
01:00:19,441 --> 01:00:21,095
[INDISTINCT LAUGHTER]

916
01:00:29,713 --> 01:00:31,062
-One for you.
-[LAUGHTER]

917
01:00:33,760 --> 01:00:35,893
What are you doing?

918
01:00:35,936 --> 01:00:38,896
Hi. We just sat down.
I didn't want to wake you.

919
01:00:38,939 --> 01:00:40,114
Give me that.

920
01:00:46,730 --> 01:00:48,209
What is the matter with you?

921
01:00:48,253 --> 01:00:49,297
What are you doing?

922
01:00:59,090 --> 01:01:01,092
What are you, crazy?
What was that all about?

923
01:01:02,876 --> 01:01:03,921
I don't know.

924
01:01:03,964 --> 01:01:05,705
Just...

925
01:01:05,749 --> 01:01:08,447
I saw the three of you there,
and something snapped.
I don't...

926
01:01:08,490 --> 01:01:09,840
I want to get rid of her.

927
01:01:09,883 --> 01:01:10,928
Anna?

928
01:01:10,971 --> 01:01:13,234
-Yes, Anna. Of course Anna.
-Why?

929
01:01:13,278 --> 01:01:15,062
Because she rearranged
your cabinets?

930
01:01:15,106 --> 01:01:17,761
Because she took Chrissy
to an amusement park?

931
01:01:17,804 --> 01:01:19,719
Yes. That and a dozen
other reasons

932
01:01:19,763 --> 01:01:21,329
that you probably are gonna
think are petty and ridiculous.

933
01:01:21,373 --> 01:01:23,767
You know, the way
her drawings inspire you.

934
01:01:23,810 --> 01:01:25,943
The way she brushes
Chrissy's hair at night,

935
01:01:25,986 --> 01:01:27,422
and whispers secrets in her ear.

936
01:01:27,466 --> 01:01:29,642
The way she makes me feel
like a stranger in my house.

937
01:01:31,383 --> 01:01:34,299
The main thing is,
I don't like her.

938
01:01:34,342 --> 01:01:36,344
And I don't think
she likes me very much.

939
01:01:45,571 --> 01:01:46,615
Okay.

940
01:01:48,269 --> 01:01:49,314
Fine.

941
01:01:50,663 --> 01:01:51,664
We'll get rid of her.

942
01:01:54,972 --> 01:01:56,451
Just like that?

943
01:01:56,495 --> 01:01:57,844
Yeah, just like that.

944
01:01:57,888 --> 01:01:59,541
I'll call the agency
first thing in the morning,

945
01:01:59,585 --> 01:02:01,152
and I will get the ball rolling.

946
01:02:03,154 --> 01:02:05,722
It could take a little while
before we get a replacement.

947
01:02:05,765 --> 01:02:07,767
Can you hang in with her
until then?

948
01:02:12,511 --> 01:02:15,253
You don't think I'm being
petty and ridiculous, do you?

949
01:02:17,168 --> 01:02:18,169
No.

950
01:02:23,217 --> 01:02:26,264
You can't help how you feel.
It's just bad chemistry,
that's all.

951
01:03:03,431 --> 01:03:04,824
-Hi.
-Hi.

952
01:03:06,086 --> 01:03:07,653
-What you doing?
-Coloring.

953
01:03:09,307 --> 01:03:10,482
Can I see?

954
01:03:13,180 --> 01:03:15,704
That's some building
you're working on.

955
01:03:15,748 --> 01:03:16,967
What is it? A castle?

956
01:03:17,010 --> 01:03:19,317
It's a church.

957
01:03:19,360 --> 01:03:22,189
Oh, yes, of course, I see.
This is the steeple, right?

958
01:03:27,412 --> 01:03:29,762
What are these?
Are these clouds?

959
01:03:29,806 --> 01:03:31,546
It's smoke.
The church is on fire.

960
01:03:35,463 --> 01:03:36,900
Well, this is interesting.

961
01:03:37,639 --> 01:03:39,641
Is that you?

962
01:03:39,685 --> 01:03:41,643
-And Daddy?
-No, that's the prince.

963
01:03:42,601 --> 01:03:43,732
The prince?

964
01:03:43,776 --> 01:03:45,604
Anna says
I'm going to marry a prince.

965
01:03:46,170 --> 01:03:47,432
Just like she...

966
01:03:48,912 --> 01:03:50,087
Just like she what, sweetheart?

967
01:03:50,130 --> 01:03:51,131
Nothing.

968
01:03:52,306 --> 01:03:53,351
Would you like one?

969
01:03:53,873 --> 01:03:54,831
Sure.

970
01:03:59,052 --> 01:04:00,575
You know, I wanted to come in,

971
01:04:01,838 --> 01:04:03,448
'cause I wanted to make sure...

972
01:04:06,190 --> 01:04:08,757
I just wanted you to know

973
01:04:08,801 --> 01:04:10,847
that I wasn't feeling
well earlier.

974
01:04:11,543 --> 01:04:13,588
But I'm all right.

975
01:04:13,632 --> 01:04:15,460
I just didn't want you
to feel scared.

976
01:04:15,503 --> 01:04:17,462
Anna said you were sleepwalking.

977
01:04:18,724 --> 01:04:21,205
I guess I was. I must have been.

978
01:04:23,033 --> 01:04:24,034
Thank you.

979
01:04:26,340 --> 01:04:28,473
Anyway, I was thinking.

980
01:04:28,516 --> 01:04:31,650
I think it would be fun
if we had a party here
for your birthday.

981
01:04:31,693 --> 01:04:33,086
Would you like that?

982
01:04:36,698 --> 01:04:38,439
-Mom?
-Hmm?

983
01:04:38,483 --> 01:04:39,919
When I grow up,

984
01:04:39,963 --> 01:04:41,965
I'm going to be an artist,
and take care of children,

985
01:04:42,008 --> 01:04:44,445
just like Anna.

986
01:04:44,489 --> 01:04:48,058
Well, I think you have
a long time to decide
things like that, don't you?

987
01:04:50,364 --> 01:04:52,236
How about some green over here?

988
01:04:54,020 --> 01:04:55,021
I guess so.

989
01:05:05,292 --> 01:05:07,947
Were you angry at Anna
for taking me
to Mystery Mountain?

990
01:05:10,428 --> 01:05:14,432
Yes, I was a little angry.
Because we had plans.

991
01:05:14,475 --> 01:05:18,392
But we're gonna have
a wonderful time at the party
tomorrow instead, aren't we?

992
01:05:22,396 --> 01:05:24,529
I'm done now.
May I be excused?

993
01:05:30,927 --> 01:05:33,190
-Hi, Bob.
-Christina, come here.

994
01:05:33,233 --> 01:05:35,105
I wanna show you something.

995
01:05:35,148 --> 01:05:37,977
-Is that for me?
-Mm-hmm. It's for your party.

996
01:05:38,021 --> 01:05:39,457
I love it. Could I put it on?

997
01:05:39,500 --> 01:05:41,502
Not right now.
I'll tell you what though.

998
01:05:41,546 --> 01:05:43,635
Why don't you take it
in the house
and show it to Anna?

999
01:05:45,245 --> 01:05:46,551
Not right now.

1000
01:05:57,127 --> 01:05:58,955
So are you feeling
any better now?

1001
01:05:59,781 --> 01:06:00,913
I guess.

1002
01:06:00,957 --> 01:06:02,610
I called the agency
this morning.

1003
01:06:04,047 --> 01:06:05,483
And?

1004
01:06:05,526 --> 01:06:07,833
Be a couple of weeks,
but they can send us a new girl.

1005
01:06:10,053 --> 01:06:12,359
-When are we gonna tell Anna?
-Whenever we want.

1006
01:06:13,012 --> 01:06:14,709
Probably a good idea

1007
01:06:14,753 --> 01:06:17,669
to wait until we know exactly
when the new one will get here.

1008
01:06:20,106 --> 01:06:23,153
You know, I didn't want things
to turn out this way.

1009
01:06:23,196 --> 01:06:26,634
I know. Like I said,
it's just bad chemistry.

1010
01:06:28,419 --> 01:06:30,943
Look what Anna gave me
to wear for my birthday.

1011
01:06:32,597 --> 01:06:35,687
Oh, honey,
you look beautiful.

1012
01:06:44,609 --> 01:06:47,612
She looks just like
a little bride, doesn't she,
Mrs. Cowan?

1013
01:07:30,742 --> 01:07:32,352
[BOTH LAUGHING]

1014
01:07:35,442 --> 01:07:36,487
It's so funny.

1015
01:07:36,791 --> 01:07:37,792
Hi.

1016
01:07:52,503 --> 01:07:53,547
Good morning.

1017
01:07:55,506 --> 01:07:57,290
Where were you all last night?

1018
01:07:57,334 --> 01:07:58,639
In the studio, painting.

1019
01:08:00,815 --> 01:08:03,470
I'm going to the office.
Where's Christina?

1020
01:08:03,514 --> 01:08:04,602
She's still sleeping.

1021
01:08:05,864 --> 01:08:07,039
When will you be home?

1022
01:08:07,083 --> 01:08:08,388
Sometime in the afternoon.

1023
01:08:15,743 --> 01:08:17,049
Now, I don't get it.

1024
01:08:17,093 --> 01:08:19,007
Nick agreed that this
little Miss Scandinavia

1025
01:08:19,051 --> 01:08:20,400
has got to go, right?

1026
01:08:20,444 --> 01:08:21,445
Right.

1027
01:08:23,011 --> 01:08:24,143
So, what's the problem?

1028
01:08:24,187 --> 01:08:25,927
The problem is,
I don't believe him.

1029
01:08:25,971 --> 01:08:28,365
I think he's just telling me
what he thinks I want to hear.

1030
01:08:30,845 --> 01:08:32,630
I woke up last night,
Nick was gone.

1031
01:08:32,673 --> 01:08:35,676
This morning,
he's in the kitchen,
all warm and cozy with Anna.

1032
01:08:35,720 --> 01:08:38,462
He says he was working
in the studio all night.

1033
01:08:38,505 --> 01:08:41,465
So you think that there might be
something going on between them?

1034
01:08:41,508 --> 01:08:44,511
I don't know what to think
anymore, Liz.
I really don't.

1035
01:08:44,555 --> 01:08:47,732
I mean, because if that's what
you're thinking,
you have to talk to him.

1036
01:08:47,775 --> 01:08:50,169
Just lay your cards out
on the table.

1037
01:08:50,213 --> 01:08:51,736
Yeah, you're right.

1038
01:08:51,779 --> 01:08:53,520
And if that doesn't work,
shoot him.

1039
01:08:57,742 --> 01:08:58,960
Thanks.

1040
01:08:59,004 --> 01:09:00,614
I'm gonna talk to him tonight.

1041
01:09:00,658 --> 01:09:01,789
No, you'll talk to him
right now.

1042
01:09:01,833 --> 01:09:03,226
No, I've got work
I've got to do now.

1043
01:09:03,269 --> 01:09:05,576
Forget about the office.
I will cover for you.

1044
01:09:05,619 --> 01:09:07,273
All right? Get out of here.
Go on.

1045
01:09:08,405 --> 01:09:09,710
I'll call you.

1046
01:09:09,754 --> 01:09:10,798
Okay.

1047
01:09:15,803 --> 01:09:16,804
Christina?

1048
01:09:17,196 --> 01:09:18,806
Hi, Mom.

1049
01:09:18,850 --> 01:09:20,417
What are you doing?

1050
01:09:20,460 --> 01:09:21,635
Get down from there.

1051
01:09:23,333 --> 01:09:24,551
Where did you get these?

1052
01:09:24,595 --> 01:09:25,683
Bob gave them to me.

1053
01:09:25,726 --> 01:09:27,163
And where's Anna?

1054
01:09:27,206 --> 01:09:28,816
I don't know. I think she went
somewhere with Daddy.

1055
01:09:28,860 --> 01:09:30,122
And left you here all alone?

1056
01:09:30,166 --> 01:09:31,689
I'm not alone. Bob's here.

1057
01:09:31,732 --> 01:09:35,040
Christina. Christina,
I'm not done talking to you.

1058
01:09:40,219 --> 01:09:41,481
Hi, Bob.

1059
01:09:41,525 --> 01:09:43,135
Hi. How are you?

1060
01:09:43,179 --> 01:09:44,180
Hello.

1061
01:09:58,933 --> 01:10:02,894
I'll take this one.
You take the other one.

1062
01:10:02,937 --> 01:10:04,809
-But don't let Christina see...
-Uh-oh.

1063
01:10:04,852 --> 01:10:05,984
Dad, what did you get?

1064
01:10:06,027 --> 01:10:08,813
No peeking, Christina.
No peeking.

1065
01:10:10,249 --> 01:10:11,294
I want to talk to you.

1066
01:10:15,080 --> 01:10:16,342
Come on, Chrissy. Let's go.

1067
01:10:21,391 --> 01:10:23,697
What the hell is going on here?

1068
01:10:23,741 --> 01:10:25,569
-What do you mean?
-What do I mean?

1069
01:10:25,612 --> 01:10:27,658
You and Anna out gallivanting
in the middle of the day?

1070
01:10:27,701 --> 01:10:29,660
We were not gallivanting.

1071
01:10:29,703 --> 01:10:30,965
We went to pick up
Chrissy's presents and get
a few things for the party.

1072
01:10:31,009 --> 01:10:32,967
And you left Chrissy here
with Bob?

1073
01:10:33,011 --> 01:10:34,273
Bob is all right.
Chrissy's crazy about him.

1074
01:10:34,317 --> 01:10:36,188
No, I don't care.

1075
01:10:36,232 --> 01:10:37,624
I don't know what's going on.
I don't know what she's
trying to do,

1076
01:10:37,668 --> 01:10:38,973
but she's not gonna get away
with it. Do you hear me?

1077
01:10:39,017 --> 01:10:40,845
What are you
talking about, Anna?

1078
01:10:42,020 --> 01:10:43,500
Are you sleeping with her?

1079
01:10:48,331 --> 01:10:50,420
You are being really ridiculous.

1080
01:10:50,985 --> 01:10:52,248
Tell me, Nick.

1081
01:10:52,944 --> 01:10:54,075
Answer me.

1082
01:10:56,469 --> 01:10:57,514
No.

1083
01:10:59,646 --> 01:11:03,041
I want that woman
out of my house.
Now. Today.

1084
01:11:03,084 --> 01:11:04,651
And what do you propose
we do with Chrissy?

1085
01:11:04,695 --> 01:11:06,087
I don't know.

1086
01:11:06,131 --> 01:11:07,350
-We'll figure out something.
-So what do we tell her?

1087
01:11:07,393 --> 01:11:08,699
That Anna had to go away

1088
01:11:08,742 --> 01:11:10,135
because Mommy
couldn't stand the competition?

1089
01:11:12,224 --> 01:11:14,357
What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

1090
01:11:14,400 --> 01:11:17,577
It means that all of this
paranoia about me and Anna
is really about you and Anna.

1091
01:11:17,621 --> 01:11:19,187
It means that maybe you're just
a little bit afraid

1092
01:11:19,231 --> 01:11:20,493
of losing your daughter
to a woman

1093
01:11:20,537 --> 01:11:22,278
who's better
at being a mother than you are.

1094
01:11:22,321 --> 01:11:24,280
You bastard.

1095
01:11:24,323 --> 01:11:26,282
I don't have time
for this, okay?

1096
01:11:27,370 --> 01:11:29,328
You want to fire her? Fire her.

1097
01:11:29,372 --> 01:11:30,677
Just leave me out of it, okay?

1098
01:11:30,721 --> 01:11:32,113
Where are you going?

1099
01:11:32,766 --> 01:11:34,159
For a ride.

1100
01:12:08,324 --> 01:12:09,325
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

1101
01:12:11,675 --> 01:12:12,719
Hello.

1102
01:12:16,462 --> 01:12:18,159
Mrs. Cowan?

1103
01:12:18,203 --> 01:12:20,074
-Yes.
-This is Stefan Grosbard.

1104
01:12:20,118 --> 01:12:22,338
You must listen to me carefully.
We don't have much time.

1105
01:12:23,382 --> 01:12:26,037
Your daughter's 
in great danger.

1106
01:12:26,080 --> 01:12:27,865
What are you talking about?
Who are you?

1107
01:12:27,908 --> 01:12:29,388
DR. GROSBARD: Please, 
just listen to me.

1108
01:12:29,432 --> 01:12:31,999
The young woman who's caring 
for your little girl,

1109
01:12:32,043 --> 01:12:34,437
she's not the real 
Anna Bergman at all.

1110
01:12:34,480 --> 01:12:36,003
She is my daughter.

1111
01:12:36,047 --> 01:12:38,876
Her name in Kirsten Grosbard, 
and she is an evil...

1112
01:12:38,919 --> 01:12:42,227
An evil young woman 
who will stop at nothing 
to get what she wants.

1113
01:12:42,270 --> 01:12:43,576
What does she want?

1114
01:12:43,620 --> 01:12:45,839
Your child, Mrs. Cowan.

1115
01:12:45,883 --> 01:12:48,407
Christina has been chosen.

1116
01:12:48,451 --> 01:12:49,582
Chosen?

1117
01:12:49,626 --> 01:12:51,715
To make a bond with the Devil.

1118
01:12:51,758 --> 01:12:53,804
This is absurd.
What are you talking about?

1119
01:12:53,847 --> 01:12:55,196
Some kind of a cult?

1120
01:12:55,240 --> 01:12:57,677
I know it's difficult
for you to understand,

1121
01:12:57,721 --> 01:12:59,287
and to believe,

1122
01:12:59,331 --> 01:13:02,073
but please, I swear to you,
what I'm saying is very real.

1123
01:13:02,116 --> 01:13:05,772
It is very real. You must 
get your daughter 
away from there.

1124
01:13:05,816 --> 01:13:10,647
Get Christina away 
from that place, 
and away from my daughter.

1125
01:13:10,690 --> 01:13:12,475
Now, is there somewhere 
we can meet?

1126
01:13:12,518 --> 01:13:14,433
I'm at LAX now.

1127
01:13:14,477 --> 01:13:16,174
Hello. Are you there?

1128
01:13:16,217 --> 01:13:18,350
Yes.

1129
01:13:18,394 --> 01:13:21,527
There's an old hotel
on Pacific Coast Highway.

1130
01:13:21,571 --> 01:13:24,530
North of Canyon Glen.
Do you know where it is?

1131
01:13:24,574 --> 01:13:27,794
I will find it,
but please hurry.

1132
01:13:28,273 --> 01:13:29,883
Please.

1133
01:13:29,927 --> 01:13:31,798
And I will pray for you, 
Mrs. Cowan.

1134
01:13:32,930 --> 01:13:34,192
I will pray for you.

1135
01:13:50,556 --> 01:13:53,124
Come on, sweetheart. Let's go.

1136
01:13:54,647 --> 01:13:55,735
Christina?

1137
01:13:57,476 --> 01:13:58,521
Christina?

1138
01:14:07,355 --> 01:14:08,444
Christina?

1139
01:14:14,145 --> 01:14:15,189
Christina?

1140
01:14:18,541 --> 01:14:19,803
Christina?

1141
01:15:24,868 --> 01:15:25,912
Nick.

1142
01:16:58,918 --> 01:17:00,354
What are you doing here?

1143
01:17:00,398 --> 01:17:02,966
I know who you are, Kirsten.
I spoke to your father.

1144
01:17:03,009 --> 01:17:04,402
Get out of this house.

1145
01:17:08,711 --> 01:17:10,103
Christina stays.

1146
01:17:12,018 --> 01:17:13,629
We'll see about that, won't we?

1147
01:17:24,291 --> 01:17:26,337
Chrissy, come on, we're leaving.

1148
01:17:26,380 --> 01:17:28,034
-Where are we going?
-We're gonna go on a trip.

1149
01:17:28,078 --> 01:17:29,732
-Just you and me.
-I don't want to go on a trip.

1150
01:17:29,775 --> 01:17:30,950
Do as you're told.

1151
01:17:30,994 --> 01:17:33,083
No. Mommy, I don't wanna go.
Let me go!

1152
01:17:33,126 --> 01:17:35,259
-Do as you're told, Christina.
-Let me go.

1153
01:17:35,302 --> 01:17:36,608
I don't wanna go.

1154
01:17:36,652 --> 01:17:38,044
-Let me go.
-Christina!

1155
01:17:39,872 --> 01:17:41,004
-Let her go.
-Let me go!

1156
01:17:42,309 --> 01:17:44,050
Don't let her do this, Nick.

1157
01:17:44,094 --> 01:17:45,573
Help me, please.

1158
01:17:45,617 --> 01:17:46,966
Anna, maybe we should tell her.

1159
01:17:47,010 --> 01:17:48,098
Shut up, Nick.

1160
01:17:48,141 --> 01:17:49,839
NICK: It's best, Kate.

1161
01:17:49,882 --> 01:17:51,928
You can't take care of Chrissy
right now.

1162
01:17:51,971 --> 01:17:53,190
CHRISTINA: Let go of me!

1163
01:17:56,149 --> 01:17:58,282
KATE: No, Christina. Christina.

1164
01:18:01,067 --> 01:18:02,329
Come with me, baby.

1165
01:18:02,765 --> 01:18:03,766
Go away.

1166
01:18:05,463 --> 01:18:06,507
Now get out.

1167
01:18:12,426 --> 01:18:13,732
I'll be back for you, baby.

1168
01:18:25,657 --> 01:18:26,832
It's all right now.

1169
01:18:27,528 --> 01:18:28,573
Go to your father.

1170
01:19:17,753 --> 01:19:19,406
Why is she doing this to us?

1171
01:19:20,277 --> 01:19:21,713
What does she want from us?

1172
01:19:21,757 --> 01:19:24,847
My daughter is fulfilling
a pact, Mrs. Cowan.

1173
01:19:24,890 --> 01:19:25,935
A pact with the Devil.

1174
01:19:28,154 --> 01:19:30,243
From each generation
he chooses a bride.

1175
01:19:30,287 --> 01:19:31,592
A little child.

1176
01:19:31,636 --> 01:19:33,681
On her eighth birthday,
she's offered, in red.

1177
01:19:33,725 --> 01:19:36,206
They put a charm
around her neck.

1178
01:19:36,249 --> 01:19:38,512
Red crystal pendant.

1179
01:19:38,556 --> 01:19:39,992
A symbol of their bond.

1180
01:19:40,036 --> 01:19:42,734
Then on her 21st birthday,
she will bear him a child.

1181
01:19:42,778 --> 01:19:44,518
She will raise the child
to maturity,

1182
01:19:44,562 --> 01:19:47,043
she will groom him to take
the positions of power.

1183
01:19:47,913 --> 01:19:49,132
Yes,

1184
01:19:49,175 --> 01:19:52,352
my daughter has spoken her vows,
Mrs. Cowan.

1185
01:19:52,396 --> 01:19:55,486
Just as yours will tonight,
unless we stop them.

1186
01:19:55,529 --> 01:19:58,228
My baby,
she wouldn't come with me.

1187
01:19:58,271 --> 01:20:00,099
Kirsten seduced her,

1188
01:20:00,143 --> 01:20:01,840
the way she seduced
your husband,

1189
01:20:01,884 --> 01:20:04,451
the way her predecessor
defrauded me

1190
01:20:04,495 --> 01:20:06,932
of my little daughter.

1191
01:20:06,976 --> 01:20:09,761
My dear wife
was driven to her grave.

1192
01:20:10,893 --> 01:20:12,764
We don't have much time.

1193
01:20:12,808 --> 01:20:14,505
My daughter has a black liturgy.

1194
01:20:14,548 --> 01:20:16,202
It's rather
like a book of rites,

1195
01:20:16,246 --> 01:20:17,769
like a children's book
of pictures.

1196
01:20:18,248 --> 01:20:19,292
My God.

1197
01:20:21,338 --> 01:20:22,469
I've seen it.

1198
01:20:22,513 --> 01:20:23,862
-[CAT SCREECHES]
-[SCREAMS]

1199
01:20:24,820 --> 01:20:26,386
-Shh.
-[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

1200
01:20:36,353 --> 01:20:37,658
Now,

1201
01:20:37,702 --> 01:20:40,444
the ceremony cannot be performed
without the book.

1202
01:20:40,487 --> 01:20:43,447
So we must find it, destroy it,
break the spell.

1203
01:20:43,490 --> 01:20:45,623
And get your daughter back.

1204
01:20:45,666 --> 01:20:46,972
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1205
01:21:06,992 --> 01:21:08,341
[GROANS]

1206
01:21:26,794 --> 01:21:28,057
[TIRES SCREECHING]

1207
01:22:06,878 --> 01:22:08,314
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1208
01:22:18,020 --> 01:22:19,238
I give thee Christina.

1209
01:22:20,239 --> 01:22:21,675
[ANNA SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1210
01:22:37,039 --> 01:22:38,214
Christina!

1211
01:22:41,043 --> 01:22:42,218
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1212
01:22:54,360 --> 01:22:55,622
Please come to me, baby.

1213
01:22:57,233 --> 01:22:58,799
Please come to Mommy.

1214
01:23:01,846 --> 01:23:03,674
Let me through, Nick.

1215
01:23:03,717 --> 01:23:04,892
She's got our little girl.

1216
01:23:05,937 --> 01:23:06,982
She'll be safe.

1217
01:23:07,852 --> 01:23:09,027
Why?

1218
01:23:09,071 --> 01:23:10,246
Tell her, Nick.

1219
01:23:12,117 --> 01:23:13,249
The future.

1220
01:23:14,206 --> 01:23:16,730
I wanted my career back.

1221
01:23:16,774 --> 01:23:18,776
And Christina
will be set for life.

1222
01:23:19,646 --> 01:23:21,126
You can join us, Kate.

1223
01:23:22,040 --> 01:23:23,781
KATE: Is that what you want?

1224
01:23:23,824 --> 01:23:26,349
For Christina to be like her?
Driven to obey?
Driven to murder?

1225
01:23:26,392 --> 01:23:28,873
For God's sake, Nick,
she had her own father killed!

1226
01:23:28,916 --> 01:23:30,222
I didn't know that.

1227
01:23:30,266 --> 01:23:31,267
[GASPS]

1228
01:23:32,137 --> 01:23:33,138
Nick!

1229
01:23:34,313 --> 01:23:36,576
Nick!
Help me, please.

1230
01:23:36,620 --> 01:23:37,838
Kate!

1231
01:23:38,230 --> 01:23:39,231
KATE: No!

1232
01:23:39,275 --> 01:23:41,016
NICK: Get off of her!

1233
01:23:41,538 --> 01:23:42,800
[GRUNTS]

1234
01:23:48,762 --> 01:23:50,199
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1235
01:24:04,691 --> 01:24:05,736
KATE: Nick!

1236
01:24:06,128 --> 01:24:09,000
No! No!

1237
01:24:12,134 --> 01:24:13,135
[GRUNTS]

1238
01:24:19,141 --> 01:24:20,490
[BOB SCREAMS]

1239
01:24:27,758 --> 01:24:28,889
KATE: Christina?

1240
01:24:31,066 --> 01:24:35,505
Christina? You can come out.
You come to Mommy now.

1241
01:24:39,813 --> 01:24:41,163
Where is she?

1242
01:24:41,206 --> 01:24:42,512
It's too late.

1243
01:24:43,165 --> 01:24:44,731
You've lost her.

1244
01:24:44,775 --> 01:24:47,299
I don't believe you.
Christina?

1245
01:24:47,343 --> 01:24:50,215
She's his servant now.
She answers only to him.

1246
01:24:50,259 --> 01:24:51,260
Mommy?

1247
01:24:52,087 --> 01:24:54,219
Christina? Honey?

1248
01:24:54,263 --> 01:24:55,568
Christina, please.

1249
01:24:55,612 --> 01:24:56,961
I love you, baby.

1250
01:24:57,004 --> 01:24:59,964
Satan loves her.
She's his bride now.

1251
01:25:01,226 --> 01:25:02,749
Christina, please.

1252
01:25:03,402 --> 01:25:04,751
Come to me, baby.

1253
01:25:05,230 --> 01:25:06,840
It's okay.

1254
01:25:06,884 --> 01:25:09,365
Stay where you are, Christina.
The Prince will be very angry.

1255
01:25:09,408 --> 01:25:11,149
You don't have to be frightened.

1256
01:25:11,193 --> 01:25:13,456
Just throw the book
in the fire, Christina.

1257
01:25:13,499 --> 01:25:14,935
I'm scared, Mommy.

1258
01:25:14,979 --> 01:25:16,459
He'll punish you, Christina.

1259
01:25:16,502 --> 01:25:18,852
-He'll hurt you very badly.
-It's okay.

1260
01:25:18,896 --> 01:25:21,159
No one's gonna
hurt you, pumpkin.

1261
01:25:21,203 --> 01:25:23,509
ANNA: Do as I say, Christina.

1262
01:25:23,553 --> 01:25:24,945
Christina!

1263
01:25:24,989 --> 01:25:25,990
Do it!

1264
01:25:27,296 --> 01:25:28,384
Chrissy.

1265
01:25:28,427 --> 01:25:29,428
No!

1266
01:25:30,429 --> 01:25:32,692
-No!
-Come to me, baby.

1267
01:25:34,303 --> 01:25:35,826
